---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`Terms of Service — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Read the ThinkingCats Terms of Service governing your use of the platform." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="compliance-main">
			<div class="compliance-inner">

				<a href="/" class="back-link">
					<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="19" y1="12" x2="5" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 19 5 12 12 5"/></svg>
					<span>Back to Home</span>
				</a>

				<div class="page-header">
					<div class="icon-badge icon-badge--violet">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon--violet"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>
					</div>
					<h1>Terms of Service</h1>
				</div>

				<div class="prose-body">

					<section>
						<h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
						<p>By accessing or using ThinkingCats, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service and all applicable laws and regulations. If you do not agree with any of these terms, you are prohibited from using or accessing this site.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
						<p>ThinkingCats provides an AI-powered brand content platform that allows agencies and marketers to create brand mascots, configure brand voice, and generate social media content at scale. All services provided are digital and non-tangible. There is no physical delivery of goods.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>3. Account Registration &amp; Google Sign-In</h2>
						<p>ThinkingCats uses Google Sign-In (OAuth 2.0) as its sole authentication method. By signing in with Google, you:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Authorise ThinkingCats to receive your Google account email address and basic profile information (name and profile picture) solely for the purpose of creating and operating your account.</li>
							<li>Confirm that you are the authorised owner of the Google account used to sign in.</li>
							<li>Agree that you are responsible for all activity that occurs under your account.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>We request only the minimum OAuth scopes required to identify you. We do not access your Gmail, Google Drive, Google Contacts, or any other Google service data. You may revoke ThinkingCats's access to your Google account at any time via <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Account Permissions</a>, which will deactivate your ability to sign in.</p>
						<p>You must be at least <strong>13 years old</strong> to create an account on ThinkingCats. By registering, you confirm that you meet this minimum age requirement. If you are under 18, you represent that you have your parent or legal guardian's permission to use the service. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If we become aware that a user is under 13, we will immediately suspend the account and delete associated data.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>4. Use License</h2>
						<p>Subject to your subscription plan, ThinkingCats grants you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable licence to access and use the platform for personal or commercial content generation. Under this licence, you may not:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Attempt to decompile, reverse-engineer, or extract the source code of any software on the platform.</li>
							<li>Use the service to generate content that is unlawful, defamatory, harassing, or fraudulent.</li>
							<li>Resell, sublicence, or white-label the platform itself without prior written agreement.</li>
							<li>Use automated scripts or bots to access the platform outside of any officially provided API.</li>
							<li>Violate any applicable laws, including but not limited to intellectual property laws.</li>
							<li>Generate synthetic media — including deepfakes, AI voice clones, or realistic AI-generated likenesses — depicting any real, identifiable individual without that individual's explicit, verifiable consent.</li>
							<li>Create content that impersonates, falsely represents, or is designed to deceive audiences into believing it was authored or endorsed by a real person, public figure, celebrity, journalist, or organisation.</li>
							<li>Generate or distribute intentional misinformation, disinformation, or fabricated news, including content designed to deceive audiences into believing it is genuine human-authored journalism, news reporting, or factual commentary.</li>
							<li>Represent or pass off AI-generated Outputs as entirely human-authored for fraudulent purposes, including in academic, journalistic, or commercial contexts.</li>
							<li>Generate sexually explicit, violent, or hateful synthetic content involving any person's likeness, real or fictional.</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>5. Synthetic Media &amp; Deepfake Policy</h2>
						<p>ThinkingCats is designed exclusively for the creation of <strong>fictional brand mascots and personas</strong>. The platform is not intended, and must not be used, to generate realistic likenesses, voices, or representations of real, identifiable individuals.</p>
						<div class="callout callout--red">
							<strong>Zero-tolerance policy:</strong> Any attempt to generate synthetic media that realistically depicts a real person's face, voice, or likeness without their verifiable, explicit consent — commonly referred to as a "deepfake" — is strictly prohibited and will result in immediate account suspension and permanent termination.
						</div>
						<p>ThinkingCats reserves the right to review, remove, and report content that violates this policy to relevant authorities. This policy is consistent with the requirements of the Apple App Store Review Guidelines (§1.1.6), Google Play Developer Policy (Misleading Content), and applicable synthetic media legislation.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>6. Misinformation &amp; Accurate Content Policy</h2>
						<p>AI-generated content may contain factual inaccuracies, outdated information, or unverified claims. You bear <strong>sole responsibility</strong> for the factual accuracy of all content you review and choose to publish using the platform.</p>
						<ul>
							<li>AI Outputs do not constitute news reporting, journalism, legal advice, financial advice, or medical advice of any kind.</li>
							<li>You must not use the platform to produce knowingly false narrative content about real people, companies, events, or matters of public concern with the intent to deceive.</li>
							<li>You must not use Outputs to manipulate public opinion, interfere with democratic processes, or spread health-related misinformation.</li>
							<li>ThinkingCats disclaims any liability for losses or damages arising from inaccurate, misleading, or harmful content published by users.</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>7. Copyright Infringement &amp; DMCA</h2>
						<p>ThinkingCats respects intellectual property rights and expects users to do the same. If you believe that content on the platform infringes your copyright, please submit a written notice containing all of the following:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Your full legal name and contact information (email, mailing address, telephone number).</li>
							<li>A description of the copyrighted work you claim has been infringed.</li>
							<li>A description of where the allegedly infringing material is located on the platform.</li>
							<li>A statement that you have a good-faith belief that the use is not authorised by the copyright owner, its agent, or law.</li>
							<li>A statement, made under penalty of perjury, that the information in your notice is accurate and that you are the copyright owner or authorised to act on their behalf.</li>
							<li>Your electronic or physical signature.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>DMCA notices should be sent to: <a href="mailto:support@thinkingcats.com">support@thinkingcats.com</a>. We will respond to valid notices promptly and, where appropriate, remove or disable access to the reported content.</p>
						<div class="callout callout--neutral">
							<strong>Repeat Infringer Policy:</strong> In accordance with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act, ThinkingCats maintains a policy of terminating the accounts of users who are determined to be repeat infringers of intellectual property rights.
						</div>
						<h3>7.1 Counter-Notification</h3>
						<p>If you believe your content was removed in error, you may submit a counter-notification to <a href="mailto:support@thinkingcats.com">support@thinkingcats.com</a> including: your contact information, identification of the removed material and its prior location, a statement under penalty of perjury that you have a good-faith belief the material was removed in error, and your consent to federal court jurisdiction.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>8. Intellectual Property &amp; AI-Generated Content</h2>

						<h3>8.1 Platform &amp; Technology</h3>
						<p>ThinkingCats, its logo, underlying AI models, algorithms, software, prompts, and all platform assets are the exclusive intellectual property of ThinkingCats. Nothing in these Terms transfers any ownership of the platform or its technology to you.</p>

						<h3>8.2 Your Input Materials</h3>
						<p>You retain full ownership of any materials you upload or provide to the platform, including persona descriptions, brand guidelines, uploaded avatar images, and RSS feed configurations ("User Inputs"). By submitting User Inputs you grant ThinkingCats a limited licence to process them solely to deliver the service. We do not claim ownership of your inputs.</p>

						<h3>8.3 AI-Generated Outputs</h3>
						<p>ThinkingCats grants you a worldwide, royalty-free licence to use, publish, and commercially exploit the posts, captions, and images generated for your account ("Outputs") for the duration of your active subscription.</p>
						<div class="callout callout--amber">
							<strong>Important — copyright in AI-generated content:</strong> Current copyright law in most jurisdictions (including the United States and the European Union) does not automatically grant copyright protection to content produced entirely by an AI system without meaningful human creative authorship. ThinkingCats <strong>does not warrant</strong> that any Output is eligible for copyright protection, nor that it is free from similarity to other existing works. You use and publish Outputs at your own discretion and risk.
						</div>

						<h3>8.4 No Third-Party IP Guarantee</h3>
						<p>AI models may produce content that resembles training data or third-party works. ThinkingCats makes no representation that Outputs are original or free from third-party intellectual property claims. You are solely responsible for reviewing Outputs before publishing and for ensuring their use does not infringe any third-party rights.</p>

						<h3>8.5 Service Improvement Licence</h3>
						<p>ThinkingCats may use anonymised, aggregated data derived from platform usage (including Output quality signals) solely to improve the service. We will not publicly attribute or reproduce your specific branded content without your consent.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>9. Disclaimer</h2>
						<p>The platform and all Outputs are provided on an <strong>'as is'</strong> basis without warranties of any kind, express or implied. ThinkingCats specifically disclaims:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Any warranty that AI-generated content is accurate, factual, original, or fit for any particular purpose.</li>
							<li>Any warranty of non-infringement of third-party intellectual property rights in generated content.</li>
							<li>Any warranty that the service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free from inaccuracies.</li>
							<li>Implied warranties of merchantability or fitness for a particular commercial purpose.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>AI-generated content may contain factual errors, bias, or unintended similarities to existing works. You are responsible for reviewing all content before publication.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
						<p>You agree to indemnify and hold ThinkingCats harmless from any claims, damages, or expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of: (a) your use of Outputs in a manner that infringes third-party intellectual property rights; (b) your violation of these Terms; or (c) content you publish using the platform.</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>11. Limitations of Liability</h2>
						<p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, ThinkingCats shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including loss of profits, data, goodwill, or business interruption, arising from your use of or inability to use the platform or any generated content, even if advised of the possibility of such damages.</p>
					</section>

					<section class="footer-note">
						<p>Last updated: March 6, 2026. For any questions regarding these terms, please contact us at support@thinkingcats.com</p>
					</section>

				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.compliance-main {
		padding: 8rem 1.5rem 5rem;
	}
	.compliance-inner {
		max-width: 768px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}
	.back-link {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
		text-decoration: none;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		transition: color 0.15s;
	}
	.back-link:hover { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); }
	.back-link svg { transition: transform 0.15s; }
	.back-link:hover svg { transform: translateX(-3px); }

	.page-header {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	}
	.page-header h1 {
		font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 5vw, 2.25rem);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		color: #fff;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.icon-badge {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 40px;
		height: 40px;
		border-radius: 12px;
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}
	.icon-badge--violet { background: rgba(139,92,246,0.1); border: 1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.2); }
	.icon--violet { color: #a78bfa; }

	.prose-body {
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
	}
	.prose-body section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
	.prose-body h2 {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
	}
	.prose-body h3 {
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
		margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;
	}
	.prose-body p { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
	.prose-body ul {
		padding-left: 1.25rem;
		margin: 1rem 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}
	.prose-body strong { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }
	.prose-body a { color: #818cf8; text-decoration: none; }
	.prose-body a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

	.callout {
		margin: 0.75rem 0 1rem;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
		line-height: 1.65;
	}
	.callout--neutral { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
	.callout--red    { background: rgba(239,68,68,0.06);   border: 1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.2); }
	.callout--amber  { background: rgba(245,158,11,0.06);  border: 1px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.2); }
	.callout strong { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); }

	.footer-note {
		padding-top: 2rem;
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
		font-size: 12px !important;
		color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3) !important;
	}
</style>
